## Errors & mistakes
- First test run used `uv run --group test` which re-resolved to Python 3.14
  (freethreaded) and tried to BUILD tiktoken 0.8.0 -> PyO3 0.22.6 max-supported
  is 3.13, build failed (code 101). The pre-existing .venv symlinked to
  cpython-3.14+freethreaded and was broken (no typing_extensions, weave import
  failed). Fixed by pinning `uv run --python 3.12` which recreated .venv as a
  working 3.12 env (235 pkgs from cache, wheels only). .venv is gitignored.
- First perl/grep invocation passed a $FILES shell var unquoted; zsh does NOT
  word-split unquoted vars, so the whole string was treated as one filename
  ("No such file or directory"). No files were modified. Redid with explicit
  file args. Lesson for this repo/shell: never rely on word-splitting in zsh.

